We also compare standard random selection of examples to the blocked form of cross-validation [12, 17], where each fold is a block of consecutive tweets. We use the following abbreviations for cross-validations:

• xval(9:1, strat, block) - 10-fold,

 stratified, blocked;

• xval(9:1, no-strat, block) - 10-fold,

 not stratified, blocked;
